<p>Is there difference in performance of the following linq queries:</p>  <pre><code> var query = from q in this.context.SomeTable             where q.SomeId == SomeId             select new SomeViewModel             {                 PrimaryAttr = q.PrimaryAttr;                 Attribute1 = q.Attribute1,                 Attribute2 = q.Attribute2,                 Attribute3 = q.Attribute3             };  query = query.OrderByDescending(q =&gt; q.PrimaryAttr).Take(5).ToList(); </code></pre>  <p>And if I filter in first the query in same line:</p>  <pre><code>var query = (from q in this.context.SomeTable             where q.SomeId == SomeId             select new SomeViewModel             {                 PrimaryAttr = q.PrimaryAttr;                 Attribute1 = q.Attribute1,                 Attribute2 = q.Attribute2,                 Attribute3 = q.Attribute3             }).OrderByDescending(q =&gt; q.PrimaryAttr).Take(5).ToList(); </code></pre>